Package gw.api.json.schema

Interface JsonSchemaProperty

public interface JsonSchemaProperty
Represents a single property delcaration from a JSON Schema file. This property could be an explicitly named property or it could be the "additionalProperties" property on a schema definition.

  • Method Details

    • getName

      @NotNull @NotNull String getName()
      Returns the name of this property, i.e. the key that it was defined with under the schema definitions "properties" object. If this JsonSchemaProperty represents the "additionalProperties" property definition, the name here will be "additionalProperties", but that behavior should not be relied on.
      Returns:
      the name of this property

    • getFullyQualifiedName

      @NotNull @NotNull String getFullyQualifiedName()
      Returns the fully-qualified name of this property, relative to the definition that contains it.

      The name will be of the form <schema-name>-<schema-version>#/definitions/<definition-name>/<property-name>

      Returns:
      the fully-qualified name of this schema property

    • getType

      @Nullable @Nullable NativeJsonType getType()
      The JSON type of the schema property. This will always be non-null if the schema property is well-formed.
      Returns:
      the JSON type of the schema property

    • getFormat

      @Nullable @Nullable String getFormat()
      The format of the schema property, if any. Only relevant if this is a scalar property.
      Returns:
      the format of the schema property, if any

    • getXGwType

      @Nullable @Nullable String getXGwType()
      The x-gw-type of the schema property, if any. Only relevant if this is a scalar property.
      Returns:
      the x-gw-type of the schema property, if any

    • getFormattedType

      @Nullable @Nullable FormattedJsonType getFormattedType()
      Returns the FormattedJsonType that combines this property's type, format, and x-gw-type. Only relevant if this is a scalar type, otherwise this will return null.
      Returns:
      the FormattedJsonType that combines this property's type, format, and x-gw-type

    • getReferencedDefinition

      JsonSchemaDefinition getReferencedDefinition()
      Returns the JsonSchemaDefinition that this property references, if any.
      Returns:
      the JsonSchemaDefinition that this property references, if any

    • getExtensions

      @NotNull @NotNull Map<String,Object> getExtensions()
      The x-gw-extensions for the property. This will always return a non-null value, though it may be empty. Values in the returned map may be null, and the map itself is immutable.
      Returns:
      the x-gw-extensions for the property

      @Nullable @Nullable JsonSchemaItems getItems()
      Returns the items declaration for this property, if any. Well-formed array properties will always have non-null items.
      Returns:
      the items for this property, if any

    • isScalar

      boolean isScalar()
      Returns true if this property has a scalar value, false otherwise. Calling getFormattedType() will return the type of scalar value.
      Returns:
      true if this property represents a scalar value, false otherwise

    • isScalarArray

      boolean isScalarArray()
      Returns true if this property has an array of scalar values, false otherwise. Calling getItems().getFormattedType() will return the type of scalar value for the array elements.
      Returns:
      true if this property represents an array of scalar values, false otherwise

    • isObject

      boolean isObject()
      Returns true if this property has an object value, false otherwise. Calling getReferencedDefinition() will return the JsonSchemaDefinition that defines the schema for the value of this property.
      Returns:
      true if this property has an object value, false otherwise

    • isObjectArray

      boolean isObjectArray()
      Returns true if this property has an array of object values, false otherwise. Calling getItems().getReferencedDefinition() will return the JsonSchemaDefinition that defines the schema of the value of elements of this property.
      Returns:
      true if this property has an object value, false otherwise
